<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CAM AIR FOUNDATION BRAKES - CLEANING AND INSPECTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CLEANING AND INSPECTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Thoroughly clean all parts except drums and brake linings in cleaning solvent and dry. The solvent
                will leave an oil residue that may affect brake performance.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Refer to the
                        <hotlnk document="s04005_1.xml" xrefid="hl0400504">warning,</hotlnk>, which applies to brake
                        lining material when servicing brakes.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <para>OSHA standards should be consulted with respect to mandatory requirements as well as for suggested
                procedures to minimize exposure.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="0">
            <title>DRUM SHOE AND LINING</title>
            <para>Refer to GROUP 04 - BRAKES in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for more detailed information.</para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
